    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> I was asking you whether you would be okay with that as an end user.\r\n\r\nIt's tough, I don't usually deal with big numbers, but I think converting to float is ok, and it is consistent with pd.to_numeric([100000000000000000000]) already doing it.\r\n\r\n> The consistency of behavior between 100000000000000000000 and [100000000000000000000]. That looks buggy to me...\r\n\r\nand '10000000000000000000000000', they all give three different results\r\n\r\nAlso strange:\r\n```python\r\npd.to_numeric([10000000000000000000000000, '10000000000000000000000000'])\r\narray([1.e+25, 1.e+25])\r\n\r\npd.to_numeric(['10000000000000000000000000'])\r\nValueError: Integer out of range. at position 0\r\n`````"
